It's 'same old Arsenal' after another under-par defensive display in the 2-1 defeat at Swansea on Sunday, according to Jamie Carragher.

The former Liverpool defender was scathing in his analysis of Arsene Wenger's tactics, even referencing his summer business in the transfer market as a reason why the club are struggling.

Arsenal threw away a goal lead with 16 minutes remaining at the Liberty, with the Welsh side scoring through Gylfi Sigurdsson and Bafetimbi Gomis.

