Wenger brought in Alexis Sanchez, Danny Welbeck, Calum Chambers and Mathieu Debuchy, but Carragher feels it wasn't enough.

'They had a better season than Chelsea, but now they feel miles apart,' he said.

'Mourinho saw areas they needed to improve and signed in those areas. Even from last season [Arsenal] look like they've gone backwards.'

